  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 01. Data Conversion (CSV to Parquet)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook handles the efficient conversion of the large `gangnam_reviews_FINAL_ALL.csv` file into a Parquet format, as per the project guidelines. This ensures faster loading and processing for subsequent analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Steps:**\n",
    "1. Load CSV using DuckDB (Streaming).\n",
    "2. Clean and Type Check.\n",
    "3. Export to Parquet."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import duckdb\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define Paths\n",
    "base_dir = Path(r'd:\\git_rk')\n",
    "raw_csv_path = base_dir / 'data' / 'gangnam_reviews_FINAL_ALL.csv'\n",
    "processed_dir = base_dir / 'data' / 'processed'\n",
    "output_parquet_path = processed_dir / 'gangnam_reviews.parquet'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ensure output directory exists\n",
    "os.makedirs(processed_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Raw CSV: {raw_csv_path}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Output Parquet: {output_parquet_path}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load & Inspect CSV with DuckDB\n",
    "We use `read_csv_auto` to infer types. `ignore_errors=True` helps skip malformed lines if any."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Connect to DuckDB (in-memory)\n",
    "con = duckdb.connect(database=':memory:')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a view or table from the CSV\n",
    "# We strictly follow the guideline: Do not load everything into python objects.\n",
    "# Let DuckDB handle the scanning.\n",
    "query = f\"\\n    CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE reviews AS \n    SELECT *\n    FROM read_csv_auto('{raw_csv_path}', ignore_errors=true, sample_size=20000)\n    \"""
    con.execute(query)
    
    "# Show schema and first few rows\n",
    "con.execute(\"DESCRIBE reviews\").show()\n",
    "con.execute(\"SELECT * FROM reviews LIMIT 5\").show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Clean & Transform\n",
    "We will:\n",
    "- Ensure `date` is correctly parsed.\n",
    "- Ensure `rating` is numeric.\n",
    "- Filter out invalid ratings (if any).\n",
    "- Select only relevant columns if needed (currently keeping all structured ones)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Example Cleaning Query (Adjust column names based on the DESCRIBE output above)\n",
    "# Assuming standard columns: hospital_id, hospital_name, review_id, nickname, rating, treatments, content, date, has_photo\n",
    "\n",
    "clean_query = \"\\n    SELECT \n        hospital_id,\n        hospital_name,\n        review_id,\n        nickname,\n        CAST(rating AS FLOAT) as rating,\n        treatments,\n        content,\n        TRY_CAST(date AS DATE) as review_date,\n        has_photo\n    FROM reviews\n    WHERE rating IS NOT NULL\n      AND content IS NOT NULL\n    \""
    
    "# Preview cleaned data\n",
    "con.execute(f\"SELECT * FROM ({clean_query}) LIMIT 5\").show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Save to Parquet"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "copy_query = f\"\\n    COPY ({clean_query}) \n    TO '{output_parquet_path}' \n    (FORMAT PARQUET, CODEC 'SNAPPY')\n    \""
    
    "con.execute(copy_query)\n",
    "print(\"Conversion complete.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Verification\n",
    "con.execute(f\"SELECT count(*) FROM parquet_scan('{output_parquet_path}')\").show()"
   ]
  }
